A popular hotelier in Ilesa, Osun State, Falola Oke, has been shot dead by some suspected assassins. Oke, was the Chief Executive Officer of Falola Hotel and Falola Rental Services in the ancient town, before his gruesome murder. The deceased was said to have been killed by the yet-to-be identified gunmen on Thursday morning. The hotelier, according to sources, was killed beside his residence at the Imo area of Ilesa. When contacted, the Public Relations Officer of the Osun State Police Command, Yemisi Opalola, did not pick the calls put across to her by our correspondent. Meanwhile, allies and friends of Oke have described his death as shocking. In his tribute, a member of the deceasedâ€™s Church, Mr. Hastrup, said he was sad to hear of his death, adding that Oke lived a short hut impactful life before he was gunned down. 